observations.recommendation:
We recommend that Management:

send letters to the concerned officers and employees demanding the immediate settlement/liquidation of their outstanding cash advances through the submission of duly accomplished liquidation reports and enforce the withholding of salary, in accordance with Section 5.1.3 of COA Circular No. 97-002 if no action is taken after the lapse of the timeline set in the demand letter; 

stop the granting of additional cash advance for travel and training to personnel with unliquidated cash advances unless the previous cash advance/s is/are fully settled;

monitor and establish controls to ensure the timely liquidation of cash advances through updated monthly aging of the same to prevent accumulation of unliquidated cash advances; and

direct the Municipal Accountant to complete the accounting of unreconciled difference between the balances in the Statement of Financial Position and the Report on Status of Unliquidated Cash Advances.

We recommend that Management:

ensure that the Report of Status of Unliquidated Cash Advances would accurately reflect the balance of outstanding cash advances as disclosed in the financial statements;

exert necessary efforts to locate the present addresses of concerned accountable officers and send them demand letters to recover the sums due them and/or update the receivable accounts; otherwise, request for write-off of validated and proven uncollectible accounts;

submit immediately to the Audit Team the related liquidation reports of the liquidated and/or settled cash advances; and 


monitor and establish controls to ensure timely liquidation of cash advances through updated monthly aging of the same to prevent accumulation of unliquidated cash advances.

We recommended that Management:

expedite the revisions of the LGU’s SWM Plan as recommended by the National SWM Commission for their approval and for LGU’s proper, clearer and systematic implementation of SWM; 

propose enough budget to be able to launch an effective intensified orientation, educational/informational briefing and the likes for SWM awareness campaign; 

assign personnel or utility workers, if necessary, to monitor and maintain sanitary landfill and other LGU’s facilities;

propose and workout ordinances with the Sangguniang Bayan that will help in the implementation of SWM;

adopt additional specific revenue-generating measure to promote the viability of the LGU’s SWM Plan;

hasten the completion of the LGU’s MRF and sanitary land fill as well as assist other barangays for them to be able to establish their own MRF; and

direct the SWM Council to closely monitor the implementation of SWM PPAs and prepare and submit Annual SWM Accomplishment Report.

We recommended that Management:
send letters to the concerned officers and employees demanding the immediate settlement/liquidation of their outstanding cash advances through the submission of duly accomplished liquidation reports and enforce the withholding of salary, in accordance with Section 5.1.3 of COA Circular No. 97-002 if no action is taken after the lapse of the timeline set in the demand letter;
stop the granting of additional cash advance for travel and training to personnel with unliquidated cash advances unless the previous cash advance/s is/are fully settled;
monitor and establish controls to ensure the timely liquidation of cash advances through updated monthly aging of the same to prevent accumulation of unliquidated cash advances; and
direct the Municipal Accountant to complete the accounting of unreconciled difference between the balances in the Statement of Financial Position and the Report on Status of Unliquidated Cash Advances.

We recommended that Management:

direct the Municipal Assessor to closely coordinate with the Provincial Assessor of the Province of Camarines Sur to raise the issue of general revision of assessment of real properties and passage of new SFMV with fully documented course of action on this matter;

assign personnel to the Office of the Municipal Treasurer, if necessary, that will focus on the account of real property owners and help in the conduct of house-to-house visit for issuance of Notice of Delinquency in the Payment of Real Property Tax to enforced collection of unpaid taxes.

We recommended and Management agreed to:
ensure that the Report of Status of Unliquidated Cash Advances would accurately reflect the balance of outstanding cash advances as disclosed in the financial statements;
exert necessary efforts to locate the present addresses of concerned accountable officers and send them demand letters to recover the sums due them and/or update the receivable accounts; otherwise, request for write-off of validated and proven uncollectible accounts;
submit immediately to the Audit Team the related liquidation reports of the liquidated and/or settled cash advances; and
monitor and establish controls to ensure timely liquidation of cash advances through updated monthly aging of the same to prevent accumulation of unliquidated cash advances.

Management shall prepare a request for write-off of dormant receivables in accordance with the applicable accounting and auditing rules and regulations.

We recommended that the Management:
expedite the revisions of the LGU’s SWM Plan as recommended by the National SWM Commission for their approval and for LGU’s proper, clearer and systematic implementation of SWM;
propose enough budget to be able to launch an effective intensified orientation/educational/informational briefing and the likes for SWM awareness campaign;
assign personnel/utility workers, if necessary, to monitor and maintain sanitary landfill and other LGU’s facilities;
propose and workout ordinances with the Sangguniang Bayan that will help in the implementation of SWM;
adopt additional specific revenue-generating measure to promote the viability of the LGU’s Solid Waste Management Plan;
hasten the completion of the LGU’s MRF and sanitary land fill as well as assist other barangays for them to be able to establish their own MRF; and
direct the SWM council to closely monitor the implementation of SWM PPAs and prepare and submit annual SWM Accomplishment Report.
